Greek Parliament Speaker Confirms Death of Athens Protester

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-10-20T15:06:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/greek-parliament-speaker-confirms-death-of-athens-protester.html
Greek lawmakers debating austerity
measures in Parliament today confirmed the death of one
protester during protests and strikes in  Athens .  “We express our condolences,” Acting Speaker Anastasios
Kourakis said in statements carried live on state-run Vouli TV.  A 53-year-old construction worker died of cardiac arrest
after a rock hit him in the head during the protests today,
Skai.gr website reported earlier, without saying how it got the
information  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  